The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has appointed Assistant Corps Marshal (ACM) Meshach Jatau as the new Zonal Commanding Officer for Osun, Oyo and Ekiti states. This was contained in a statement issued by the spokesman of the zone, Kolawole Alabi, on Tuesday in Osogbo, Osun State. The new zonal commander was at various times the Registrar of the FRSC Academy; Sector Commander in Abia and Rivers; Commandant, Inspectorate Training School; Director of Studies, FRSC Command and Staff College; and Principal Corps Officer to the Corps Marshal. Jatau is a Fellow of the Nigerian Army War College and a member of Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA). (NAN)